## 8. `fillTextInput()` — Complete (form-detector.js:497-556)

```js
// form-detector.js lines 497-556
async fillTextInput(el, field, value) {
  const fieldLabel = field.label || field.name || 'field';
  const isOracle = this.isOracleCXField(el);

  if (isOracle) {
    // Oracle CX: paste approach (InputEvent insertFromPaste)
    el.focus();
    console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → Oracle CX, using paste`);
    try {
      el.focus();
      el.value = '';
      el.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
      el.value = value;
      el.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', {
        inputType: 'insertFromPaste',
        data: value,
        bubbles: true,
        cancelable: true,
      }));
      el.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
      el.blur();
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 200));
      if (el.value === value) {
        console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → paste OK`);
        return true;
      }
      console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → paste: value didn't stick, falling back to char-by-char`);
    } catch(e) {
      console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → paste error: ${e.message}, falling back`);
    }

    // Fallback: char-by-char
    try {
      el.focus();
      el.value = '';
      el.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
      for (let i = 0; i < value.length; i++) {
        el.value = value.substring(0, i + 1);
        el.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 20));
      }
      el.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
      el.blur();
      if (el.value === value) {
        console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → char-by-char fallback OK`);
        return true;
      }
    } catch(e) {
      console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → char-by-char fallback error: ${e.message}`);
    }
  }

  // NOT Oracle CX → only paste approach tried through the Oracle branch;
  // if non-Oracle, no strategies attempted at all!
  console.log(`JC: fillField [${fieldLabel}] → ALL strategies failed`);
  return false;
}
```

**Critical issue**: For non-Oracle-CX text inputs, `fillTextInput()` does **nothing** — it only has strategies inside the `if (isOracle)` block. The function reaches the bottom and returns `false` for any non-Oracle field. This means `fillField()` → `fillTextInput()` fails silently for Workday, Greenhouse, Lever, etc. text inputs that reach this path.

Wait — let me re-examine. The `fillField()` router calls `fillTextInput()` only for non-combobox, non-select, non-file inputs. And `fillTextInput()` only does work inside `if (isOracle)`. So for non-Oracle platforms, text inputs are NOT filled by this function.

But looking at `fillField()`, there's the comment about Strategy 1, 2, 3, 4 in the docstring. Those strategies are NOT implemented in the actual code! The function doesn't have the native prototype setter (Strategy 2) or the char-by-char for non-Oracle (Strategy 3/4). Those strategies seem to have been removed or never added. The only working path is the Oracle-specific paste+char-by-char path.

