## 3. Search for `unprocessed`/`unknown`/`fallback`/`catch-all` fill logic

**Result: NONE EXISTS.** There is no function that catches unrecognized field names and tries to fill them anyway. The `unknown` bucket in `FormDetector.detect()` (line 189-217) collects fields that scored no pattern match, but `fillPersonal()` only iterates `fields.personal` and `fields.selects` — it never touches `fields.unknown`.

The only "catch-all" is:
