## 4. `fillField()` — router logic

**File:** `extension/content/form-detector.js`, lines 402-441 (exact function)

```
async fillField(field, value) {          // LINE 402
    if (!field || !field.el) return false;
    const el = field.el;
    const valueStr = (value || '').trim();
    if (!valueStr) return false;

    el.focus();

    // ── SELECT (native dropdown) ──
    if (el instanceof HTMLSelectElement) {          // LINE 412
      return this.fillSelect(el, valueStr);
    }

    // ── FILE (cannot set programmatically) ──
    if (el.type === 'file') return false;           // LINE 416

    // ── ORACLE CUSTOM COMBOBOX ──
    const hasToggle = document.getElementById(el.id + '-toggle-button');
    if (this.isOracleCombobox(el) && (el.type !== 'text' || hasToggle)) {   // LINE 420
      return await this.fillOracleCombobox(el, valueStr);
    }

    // ── TEXT INPUTS / TEXTAREAS: Fallback chain ──
    return await this.fillTextInput(el, field, valueStr);   // LINE 424
  }
```

**Router decision chain:**
1. Native `<select>` → `fillSelect()` (3-phase matching)
2. File upload → return false (cannot set)
3. Oracle combobox (role=combobox + inside `.cx-select`/`.cx-select-container`) → `fillOracleCombobox()` (4 strategies)
4. Everything else (text, email, tel, url, number, textarea) → `fillTextInput()` (paste→char-by-char)

**`fillTextInput()`** (lines 468-550): For Oracle CX fields → paste via InputEvent `insertFromPaste`, fallback char-by-char. For non-Oracle → just sets `el.value` directly. Note: non-Oracle text inputs only get **Strategy 1** (direct assignment) — no char-by-char fallback outside Oracle.

